name: Malala Yousafzai
achievements: Nobel Peace Prize winner; advocate for girls' education
quote: One child, one teacher, one book, one pen can change the world.

name: Ada Lovelace
achievements: First computer programmer; created an algorithm for Charles Babbage's early computer
quote: That brain of mine is something more than merely mortal; as time will show.

name: Marie Curie
achievements: First woman to win a Nobel Prize; discovered polonium and radium
quote: Nothing in life is to be feared, it is only to be understood.

name: Wangari Maathai
achievements: Nobel Peace Prize winner; founded the Green Belt Movement
quote: It's the little things citizens do. That's what will make the difference.

name: Katherine Johnson
achievements: NASA mathematician; calculated trajectories for the Apollo missions
quote: Like what you do, and then you will do your best.

name: Rosalind Franklin
achievements: Contributed to discovering the DNA double helix structure
quote: Science and everyday life cannot and should not be separated.

name: Indira Gandhi
achievements: First and only female Prime Minister of India
quote: You cannot shake hands with a clenched fist.

name: Jane Goodall
achievements: Revolutionized the study of primates; UN Messenger of Peace
quote: What you do makes a difference, and you have to decide what kind of difference you want to make.

name: Oprah Winfrey
achievements: Media mogul; philanthropist; advocate for education and self-improvement
quote: Turn your wounds into wisdom.

name: Hedy Lamarr
achievements: Inventor of frequency-hopping technology; Hollywood actress
quote: Hope and curiosity about the future seemed better than guarantees.

name: Ruth Bader Ginsburg
achievements: Supreme Court Justice; advocate for gender equality
quote: Fight for the things that you care about, but do it in a way that will lead others to join you.

name: Amelia Earhart
achievements: First female aviator to fly solo across the Atlantic Ocean
quote: The most difficult thing is the decision to act; the rest is merely tenacity.

name: Ellen Johnson Sirleaf
achievements: First elected female head of state in Africa; former president of Liberia
quote: If your dreams do not scare you, they are not big enough.

name: Mae Jemison
achievements: First African American woman in space
quote: Never be limited by other people's limited imaginations.

name: Margaret Thatcher
achievements: First female Prime Minister of the United Kingdom
quote: Being powerful is like being a lady. If you have to tell people you are, you aren't.

name: Frida Kahlo
achievements: Iconic artist known for her self-portraits and works on identity and suffering
quote: I paint myself because I am so often alone and because I am the subject I know best.

name: Angela Merkel
achievements: First female Chancellor of Germany; influential EU leader
quote: Always be more than you appear and never appear to be more than you are.

name: Kamala Harris
achievements: First female, Black, and South Asian Vice President of the United States
quote: I may be the first, but I will not be the last.

name: Serena Williams
achievements: Tennis champion with 23 Grand Slam titles; advocate for women's rights
quote: I am lucky that whatever fear I have inside me, my desire to win is always stronger.

name: Sheryl Sandberg
achievements: COO of Facebook; advocate for women in leadership
quote: What would you do if you weren't afraid?
